data(nyc_airbnb)

Brainstorm questions

Where are max and min air bnb prices? what are average prices? Where are prices going up and down over time? Whats the relationship between number of reviews and average review? Does room type affect availability? Whats the location of the unit? What area are popular? Popularity = number of units? Average price? Are there repeat hosts? If so, what does that mean?

nyc_airbnb |>
  ggplot(aes(x = review_scores_location, y = price)) +
  geom_point()
## Warning: Removed 10037 rows containing missing values or values outside the scale range
## (`geom_point()`).

nyc_airbnb |>
  filter(neighbourhood_group == "Manhattan",
         price < 1000) |>
  ggplot(aes(x = lat, y = long, color = price)) +
  geom_point(alpha = .1)

nyc_airbnb |>
   filter(neighbourhood_group == "Manhattan",
   price < 1000,
   room_type == "Entire home/apt") |>
  group_by(neighbourhood) |>
  summarize(mean_price = mean(price)) |>
  arrange(desc(mean_price))
